                <h1>Discover Fascinating Italy: Facts You Never Knew</h1>
                <p>Italy, a country rich in history and culture, boasts numerous fascinating facts. It is home to the smallest country in the world, Vatican City, and boasts the most UNESCO World Heritage Sites. The Italian language is a descendant of Latin, and Italy is famous for its contributions to art, fashion, and cuisine, including global favorites like pizza and pasta.</p>
